
# WebDAV Impersonate – Windsurf Rules

## Project Context
- Nextcloud App (PHP 8.1+, Nextcloud 28+)
- App ID: webdav_impersonate
- Namespace: OCA\WebDavImpersonate
- License: AGPL-3.0-or-later (ALL files must have AGPL header)

## Code Standards
- PSR-12 coding style, strict_types=1 in every PHP file
- Only use OCP\* interfaces, never OC\* internal classes
- Dependency injection via constructor, never static calls
- PHPUnit 10 for all tests, mock all dependencies
- Comprehensive inline documentation for all methods and classes
- Use PHPDoc blocks with @param, @return, @throws annotations
- Document all public methods with purpose, parameters, and examples

## File Conventions
- Keep docs/developer.md and docs/setup.md always up to date
- Maintain a TODO.md with [TODO] [IN PROGRESS] [DONE] status
- Every new class needs a corresponding unit test

## Architecture Rules
- DAV Plugin registers via SabrePluginAddEvent (NOT hooks)
- Admin settings use OCP\Settings\ISettings interface
- Config stored via IConfig::setAppValue/getAppValue
- Logging only through LoggerInterface, never error_log()

## Feature Requirements
- WebDAV user impersonation via header parameter
- Admin configuration UI for allowed groups
- Group selection with autocomplete
- Configurable log levels in admin settings
- Comprehensive logging of impersonation actions
- Nextcloud App Store compliance

## Development Workflow
- Create unit tests for all new classes
- Update documentation during development
- Ensure AGPL license headers on all files
- Follow Nextcloud App Store guidelines
- Implement proper error handling and logging

